name: Ready Mixed Concrete (LWC 3000-4000psi)
description: Like normal weight concrete, structural lightweight concrete is highly customizable in composition.  In general, lightweight concretes rely on lighter aggregates (both course and fine) and can use air entraining admixtures to add substantially more air to the concrete than is typically seen in NWC of the same strength. Depending on the specifications, a portion of the fine lightweight aggregate can be replaced with sand, but this improvement in strength comes at an increase in weight.  This Common Product profile describes the composition of a lightweight 3,000 – 4,000 psi concrete for construction in the San Francisco Bay area.
